   "body" : "As a reference issue https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/28159 has additional details and rationale. This PR adds an additional if case to bech32.cpp LocateErrors to account for the Bech32 string too short case. This clears up ambiguity where a Bech32 string that doesn't meet the specs of BIP173 and then generates a separator position or missing error when a < 8 char string is presented. This was discovered while checking and running the src/test/bech32_tests.cpp file. \r\n\r\nAdding this case would make DecodeDestination more accurate or anyone who wants to to implement bech32.{cpp,h}",
